<br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2455.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Ro's Fiery Sundering</span><hr size=1> I am level 40.2 and i managed to pick up a copy of this great spell last night for 500 plat.  I think that it kicks ass, and i tested it on some red drovlargs(SP) in dreadlands and all my nukes landed for full, but in the fervor i did overargo and die=(<br>
<br>
anyway, im really pumped that i got a spell that some wait until they are 50+ to get=) as a side thought i was wondering...how much could i have sold the spell for on the market?  i played on cazic thule and everyone knows of the messed up market we got.<br>
<br>
another question, does lightning strike count as magic save or fire save?  it sounds stupid but it gives a fire animation when i hit those lovely OT mobs with it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umallansouthpaw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MallanSouthpaw</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#333399>(6/1/01 11:12:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2455.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ro's Fiery Sundering</span><hr size=1> LS is magic-based.<br>
<br>
Before they upped the drop rate on RFS, I saw it go for anywhere from 5k to 30k on Innoruuk.  I still haven't seen it being sold a lot (I got one off a ry`gorr elite at the orc fort shortly after the last patch), so I'd guess the price has come down some, but it's still prolly worth at least 1-2k.<br>
<br>
As a side note, the aggro from RFS seems to be proportional to the level of the mob.  I was casting Ensnare and RFS on mobs while grouped with a52 monk, and the green/lower mobs would turn to aggro on him MUCH sooner than the blue/higher mobs.  A friend went on a Hate raid and said that if he snared and RFS'd a mob there, it would take more than 30 seconds of a full hate raid group to get the mob off him.<br>
<br>
-Mallan Southpaw<br>
54 Wanderer, Legacy of Honour<br>
Innoruuk <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubainwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bainwolf</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 118<br> <font color=#333399>(6/1/01 2:31:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2455.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ro's Fiery Sundering</span><hr size=1> I must say I really love this spell.  Like someone said before &quot;Its a lvl 59 spell disguised as a lvl 39&quot;.  As for aggro control<br>
1. let the rangers snare<br>
2. distance<br>
3. timing<br>
<br>
I use this spell quite effectively in ToV.  I tend to cast it at the begining of a fight, typically after tash and/or malo and then I wait a bit, I am usually as far away from the mob as I can be.  Then  Breath of Ro followed by Wildfires, as long as I dont chaincast I wont get summoned.  I have been playing around with the timing to see how fast I can cast Wildfire without getting summoned.  Its nice seeing Wildfire hit for full time after time.<br>
<br>
Price on spell pre-patch 5k - 15k.  After patch its still going for around 1 - 2k.  I expect the price to level around 500-1k maybe even lower once every Druid has one, it is dropping quite frequently now. <br>
<br>
Bainwolf <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usyldane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>syldane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#333399>(6/1/01 11:29:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2455.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ro's Fiery Sundering</span><hr size=1> If you wait for about 10% damage to a mob by the other party members before casting Ro's Fiery it usually has enough hate to keep you from being at the top of the Hate List.  The suggestion to have a ranger or perhaps another druid snare is a good one, as the snare + Ro's Fiery almost guarantees you top billing on the mobs &quot;Must Kill&quot; list.  If I time it out, I can put up Ro's Fiery, wait a few seconds, then toss Breath of Ro, wait a few seconds, then drop a starfire or two (only 52nd so far) and still avoid most summons.  However, I have cast Ro's Fiery on mobs with 50% damage already and got pulled and smacked around, so there is always some risk involved when you have summoning creatures.  And be prepared to die if your main tank (that has been taunting it off of you) should suddenly get killed, because that mob is coming straight for the debuffing druid more than likely.  I had that happen in Kael and it was NOT a pretty sight.<br>
<br>
Pricing on Rallos:  It's been dropping like flies everywhere.  I've seen several for sale for 500pp, one even for 100, but he said he wasn't worried about gouging anyone.  With the additional debuffing on PvP now though, they may be even MORE in demand than before. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uszaero.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Szaero</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#333399>(6/3/01 1:17:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2455.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ro's Fiery Sundering</span><hr size=1> Bought mine finally for 100p the other day.  Second time it was offered at this price.. the first time, the guy discovered he had already sold it when he offered it to me. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubuteaoregalis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ButeaoRegalis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 66<br> <font color=#333399>(6/4/01 8:43:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2455.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ro's Fiery Sundering</span><hr size=1> I'd be surprised if it was more than 100pp. I certainly wouldn't have paid any more than that once they started dropping like mad. My then-37 enchanter went to the Tower of Frozen Shadows for a few nights and we saw at least 6 copies drop (3rd and 4th floors for the most part).<br>
<br>
Buteao<br>
52 Druid on Xegony <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaelwr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aelwr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 130<br> <font color=#333399>(6/4/01 9:13:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2455.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ro's Fiery Sundering</span><hr size=1>  I got my copy from the 4th Librarian on the second floor. I was just trying to get a key. So my trip was cut short. As for aggro it does aggro some but not nearly as much as healing, Snare, Fixation of Ro, or other spells of that nature. I did get hit a couple of times while using it but i would get hit a lot more often casting snare first on similar MOBs. Waiting a little to let the melee classes to get some aggro worked well and I never got hit just casting this if I waited for it to lose 10% or so health first. <br>
<br>
 On aggro I found the best way to die against a high HP summoning creature is to snare, then heal the cleric it is currently beating on because of over aggroing healing. I would always prefer for a Ranger to snare duing a big encounter because snaring then chain healing to keep someone alive will almost always get me summoned and then usually killed. It seems if I am just aggro from the heals and not from snaring usually they can taunt it off before I die. <br>
<br>
Aelwr 55th Druid <br>
Innoruuk <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udaeddwin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daeddwin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 564<br> <font color=#333399>(6/19/01 9:02:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2455.topic&index=7>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ro's Fiery Sundering</span><hr size=1> I've heard that Ro's is dropping off of Ulthork's in the Eastern Wastes since the drop-rate was increased.  Can anybody tell me if it drops off of any Ulthork, or a specific kind?  I brought a few guildies to EW to kill some Ulthorks to help level, and to see if we could get the spell to drop.  I'm about 4 blue bubbles away from being able to use it.<br>
<br>
