Officer of <i>Spirit of Norrath</i><br>
<b>Lanys T'yvl</b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaerynn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aerynn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#333399>(6/19/01 12:28:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2455.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.facelink.com/Aerynn?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ro's Fiery Sundering</span><hr size=1> Daeddwin, it's dropping occasionally from the Ulthork Man'o'wars.  I don't think the Warriors or Hunters are high enough to be included in the loot table for the dropped spells.  I personally haven't seen one drop from the MoWs despite hours of killing there, but the guy I bought my copy from said that's where he got it.  (20pp - couldn't resist that price!) <br>
<br>
I've seen a really good drop rate on the spell in Tower of Frozen Shadow, though.  We did a raid there the weekend after I bought my spell with our sister guild and had 6 copies of the spell drop in 4 hours.  (Two copies of Turning of the Unnatural, as well.) We were holding the fifth floor wedding party and the golem ushers from the entrance.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps!  It's a really great spell.<br>
