Officer of <i>Spirit of Norrath</i><br>
<b>Lanys T'yvl</b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usilleyeskimo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SilleyEskimo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 381<br> <font color=#333399>(6/19/01 4:00:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2455.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ro's Fiery Sundering</span><hr size=1> On Veeshan in NFP, I saw it auctioned 3 times in 2 hours.  I asked each seller what the price was and all 3 wanted me to offer.  I had 2 accept 20pp, and one laugh at me saying it was worth 10k.  I didn't even bother to respond, heh.  The drop rate is great on this spell.  I was actually thinking they would nerf the drop rate because it is so common now.  That's not a bad thing at all:)  It's a good time to be a druid near level 39...will save you much grief.<br>
